list and militarist attitudes before the war, struggled to adapt to the new internationalist climate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPopular culturezGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aPopular culturezGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 4aStudies in Imperialism 2017. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aBritish imperialism.  aEdwardian times.  aEmpire Marketing Board.  aGirl Guides.  aScout movement.  aVictorian children's books.  aeducation.  aimperial economic vision.  aimperialist ideologies.  ainterwar years.  ajuvenile fiction.  ajuvenile literature.  alate-Victorian times.  amass reading public.  anationalist ideologies.  apopular art.  apopular culture.  apublic school systems.  astate school systems.1 aBratton, J. S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConstantine, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacKenzie, John M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMangan, J. A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichards, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShephard, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpringhalt, John O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSummerfield, Penny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarren, Allen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611956840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526119568423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526119568/origi